{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, improving energy efficiency, promoting the utilization of renewable building materials, and conservation of resources are essential for achieving carbon neutrality in the construction industry.",
    "The shift away from traditional building materials like cement, steel, and bricks toward sustainable and eco-friendly biomaterials will benefit ecological preservation.",
    "As an innovative approach, biomaterials offer a new perspective on construction materials, harnessing the potential of organic substances, agricultural by-products, and waste materials (Freitas et al. 2021).",
    "The diverse range of biomaterials encompasses bioplastics (Oberti and Paciello 2022), biocomposites (Li et al. 2022), biocement (Yu et al. 2022), mycelium-based materials (Bitting et al. 2022), and more.",
    "Bioplastics provide eco-friendly alternatives for interior finishes, promoting healthier indoor environments (Hwang et al. 2020)."
  ]
}